import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['delay'] = pd.to_numeric(data['delay'], errors='coerce')
    plt.hist(data['delay'], bins=50, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='red', label='Median delay: {:.2f}'.format(data['delay'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance'].plot(kind='box')
    plt.axhline(y=data['distance'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='-')
    plt.legend(['Average distance: {:.2f}'.format(data['distance'].mean())])
    plt.title('What is the average distance of flights?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['origin'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar', color='blue', alpha=0.5, label='Origin')
    data['destination'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar', color='red', alpha=0.5, label='Destination')
    plt.title('Which airports have the highest number of flights?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.scatter(data['distance'], data['delay'], alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Distance (miles)')
    ax.set_ylabel('Delay (minutes)')
    ax.set_title('What is the relationship between flight distance and delay time?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data.groupby('date').size().reset_index(name='count')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['count'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight dates?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
